  "response": "To find a freight forwarder in Russia, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. Online directories and platforms:\n- Russian Cargo Association website\n- Russian Chamber of Commerce and Industry\n- B2B platforms like Alibaba or GlobalTrade\n- Trade.gov Russia's business directories\n\n2. Professional networks:\n- LinkedIn\n- FIATA (International Federation of Freight Forwarders Associations)\n- Professional logistics groups on social media\n\n3. Trade shows and exhibitions:\n- TransRussia Logistics Exhibition\n- International Transport and Logistics Exhibition\n- Cargo and Transportation Exhibitions\n\n4. Recommended resources:\n- Google search with specific keywords\n- Industry-specific websites\n- Recommendations from international trade associations\n\n5. Specific companies to research:\n- GEFCO Russia\n- FM Logistic\n- Kuehne + Nagel Russia\n- DHL Global Forwarding Russia\n- Panalpina Russia\n\n6. Verification steps:\n- Check company credentials\n- Verify licenses and certifications\n- Read client reviews and testimonials\n- Request references\n- Compare multiple providers\n\n7. Consider working with international freight forwarders with Russian operations for potentially smoother interactions.",
